Two men have appeared in court for dealing in illicit cigarettes.
Mohamed Osman, 36, and Adam Bhiku, 25, had been arrested on December 13 by the Hawks and Crime Intelligence Unit for dealing in illicit cigarettes and were found operating in different areas.
The Hawks said in a statement that their arrest had come after a systematic investigation by Port Shepstone Organised Crime Hawks members and other role players.
READ: Six arrested after police seize illegal cigarettes worth R18m
Picture: Supplied

"During the operation 376 master cases of illicit cigarettes with the street value of approximately (R5 million) were confiscated. Among the items seized were one rifle, a Mercedes Vito panel van and R13 000 in cash."
They said that Osman had appeared in the Newcastle Magistrates’ Court on December 14 and had been granted R7 500 bail. His  case was postponed to January 25. Bhiku appeared in the Pietermaritzburg Magistrates’ Court on December 14 and was remanded in custody.


That case was adjourned to December 19 for bail application.
The Mercury
